The paper discusses the application of search-based software testing (SBST) in an industrial setting and the development of the Interactive Search-Based Software Testing (ISBST) system. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of NASA Task Load Index (NASA-TLX) to assess the workload experienced by participants, which could fall under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the use of a tool to assess human performance.
